**Common backbone idea:** Both algorithms identify bottleneck jobs by computing a criticality score that combines the coefficient of variation of processing times across machines with a conflict measure derived from neighboring jobs in the current sequence, then perturb those jobs’ processing times using linear scaling.

**New algorithm description:**  
{The new algorithm identifies bottleneck jobs by computing the sum of pairwise absolute processing-time differences between each job and all others in the sequence (global conflict), then applies a non-linear exponential perturbation (multiply by e^{±0.5}) to the selected jobs’ times.}

